      • authenticate

        void authenticate(Context context,
                String token,
                WeemoEngine.UserType userType)
        Asynchronous call.
        Connects to servers with the given userId.
        An AuthenticatedEvent will be fired upon user authentication.
        Parameters:
        context - The Context to use
        token - The token that authenticate this user
        userType - The type of the user
        Throws:
        WeemoIllegalArgumentException - if context, userId or userType is null
        WeemoIllegalArgumentException - if Weemo.getEngineStatus() is already WeemoEngine.Status.AUTHENTICATED, WeemoEngine.Status.CONNECTED or WeemoEngine.Status.NETWORK_LOST.

      • disconnect

        void disconnect()
        Disconnects the WeemoEngine.
        The WeemoEngine runs in the background and can consume battery. This call stops it.
        Warning : After this call, Weemo.instance() will return null until you call Weemo.initialize(String, Context) to re-create the WeemoEngine.
        A ConnectedEvent will be fired upon disconnection with ConnectedEvent.Error.CLOSED value.

      • overrideEncodingParameters

        void overrideEncodingParameters(int maxFps,
                              int maxBitrate,
                              int resolutionDivider)
        Synchronous call.
        Overrides the video encoding parameters.
        Callable anytime after Weemo has been initialized.
        Parameters are retained until next call. If a parameter is set to 0, its default behaviour is restored.
        Parameters:
        maxFps - maximum framerate [1-30] fps.
        maxBitrate - maximum bitrate in bps [1-1000000] bps.
        resolutionDivider - [1-2]. If 2, output resolution will be downscaled by 2 in width and height, before encoding.

      • overrideEncodingParametersAdvanced

        void overrideEncodingParametersAdvanced(int opusComplexity,
                                      int opusBitrate,
                                      int vp8CpuUsage)
        Synchronous call.
        Overrides the advanced video encoding parameters.
        Callable anytime after Weemo has been initialized. Parameters are retained until next call.
        Default values are:
        • opusComplexity: 4
        • opusBitrate: 24000
        • vp8CpuUsage: 8
        Parameters:
        opusComplexity - [0 lowest-10 highest]
        opusBitrate - bitrate [16000-64000] bps.
        vp8CpuUsage - [0 intensive-16 minimum cpu usage]

      • goToBackground

        void goToBackground()
        Indicates that you wish to put the WeemoEngine in background mode.

        In background mode, the SDK will consume less battery (It will still receive calls).
        You must call goToForeground() before doing anything else in the SDK. Even when you receive a new call, you must call it before WeemoCall.resume().

        Using this is optional.
        Throws:
        WeemoIllegalStateException - if the SDK is already in background mode
        See Also:
        goToForeground()

      • goToForeground

        void goToForeground()
        Indicates that you wish to put the WeemoEngine back in foreground mode.
        Throws:
        WeemoIllegalStateException - if the SDK is already in foreground mode
        See Also:
        goToBackground()

      • isInBackground

        boolean isInBackground()
        Returns:
        true if the WeemoEngine is currently in background mode.
        See Also:
        goToBackground(), goToForeground()
